{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/1302/comments/13025202.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/1302#comment-13025202"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/1302.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 1302, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}ts=1694483"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gazebo", "full_name": "osrf/gazebo", "uuid": "{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}"}, "title": "Universal time"}, "content": {"raw": "This doesn't seem to cause an error when used within a WorldPlugin:\n\n```c++\n\npublic: void Load(physics::WorldPtr world, sdf::ElementPtr root)\n{\n\tcommon::Time offset;\n\toffset.sec  = 1413470509;\n\toffset.nsec = 0.1;\n\tworld->SetSimTime(offset);\n}\n\n```\n\nAlthough, I'm not sure if that's the right way to go about doing things. For example, Is there a guarantee on what order the world plugins are loaded? Can I ensure that the simulation time is set prior to other world plugins loading?\n", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>This doesn't seem to cause an error when used within a WorldPlugin:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-c++\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"k\">public</span><span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">void</span> <span class=\"n\">Load</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">physics</span><span class=\"o\">::</span><span class=\"n\">WorldPtr</span> <span class=\"n\">world</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">sdf</span><span class=\"o\">::</span><span class=\"n\">ElementPtr</span> <span class=\"n\">root</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"p\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">common</span><span class=\"o\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Time</span> <span class=\"n\">offset</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">offset</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sec</span>  <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"mi\">1413470509</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">offset</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">nsec</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"mf\">0.1</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">world</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"n\">SetSimTime</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">offset</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>Although, I'm not sure if that's the right way to go about doing things. For example, Is there a guarantee on what order the world plugins are loaded? Can I ensure that the simulation time is set prior to other world plugins loading?</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2014-10-16T14:50:32.536628+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Andrew Symington", "uuid": "{db1311fc-02e6-442e-84a1-4bb85dfee5ba}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bdb1311fc-02e6-442e-84a1-4bb85dfee5ba%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bdb1311fc-02e6-442e-84a1-4bb85dfee5ba%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:cab3b56e-7c24-487c-b07f-05e0600adf54/8a009f21-29b8-4d43-98ed-2677428e17ff/128"}}, "nickname": "asymingt", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:cab3b56e-7c24-487c-b07f-05e0600adf54"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 13025202}